A Fabry–Pérot interferometer differs from a Fabry–Pérot etalon in the fact that the distance &quot;ℓ&quot; between the plates can be tuned in order to change the wavelengths at which transmission peaks occur in the interferometer. Due to the angle dependence of the transmission, the peaks can also be shifted by rotating the etalon with respect to the beam.

